		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=35651"><span id=Guru>Keyeluke</span></a><b><span id=Guru><br>Guru</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>684 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Emerging consensus, or at least emerging reports, suggest that we're taking an average 10-15% increase in damage (or DPS, if you want to be technical) from mobs now.&nbsp;&nbsp;Very high end monks (those in NToV gear with crazy high AC) aren't seeing a difference, but all others are.<br><br>I see a difference, personally.  I have been soloing spiders in Velks for a while now, and I end up with somewhat more down time.  Under good circumstances, I used to be able to get 6 blue of AA per hour - it's more like 5 now. <br><br>Damage is definitely uneven - lots of hits for max damage, and a lot of hits for mid-range damage.  Combine that with our avoidance, and in some fights I get hardly scratched (as before) and in some fights I get snotted hard.<br><br>Some people were speculating that our avoidance was upped.  I don't buy that rumor - no evidence other than wishful thinking there.<br><br>I believe their stated goals don't match what they did.  They wanted to reduce the monk's effectiveness as a tank in end-game encounters (end-game monks, by virtue of +100hp items, end up with hit point pools high enough to theoretically make them effective tanks).  Instead, they hurt the mitigation of ALL BUT the end-game tanks.  This affects the soloer most of all.  Since <br>Verant seems to dislike soloing, they're not too bothered by this, it appears.<br><br>The thing that bothers me most about this is the response from many players of other classes.  I've had guildmates cheering in happiness over this.  These are people who are supposed to be friends and players pursuing a common goal.  They're happy that my game-play has been gimped somewhat, and start up with nonsense that &quot;we had it coming&quot; and that &quot;we shouldn't be able to solo&quot; (why the hell not?).  I remember those people who were happy over this, and when it comes time to help them with their personal goals, maybe I won't be available.</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Keyeluke<br>Member of Tenacity - Druzzil Ro<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td class=mhback align=right><span class=mh id=fs8><a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=3><img src=/shared/root_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Up" width=17 height=11> Thread Index</a> |  <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=3&post=1><img src=/shared/new_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="New" width=17 height=11> New Subject</a> | <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=3&mid=10353975551446&num=2&post=1&mid=10353975551446><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply" width=17 height=11> Reply to Thread</a></span></td></tr><tr><td><table width=100% border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 class=mform><tr><td colspan=1  style='font-size: 9.5px;'>2 Posts [ <a href="/fsearch.html?base=class3">Search Forums</a> ]</nobr></td></tr></table>&nbsp;</td></tr>
